text: Choi Min-kyu (; born August 31, 1992) is a South Korean sprint canoeist. He competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the men's K-2 200 metres race with Cho Kwang-hee; the two placed ninth. ==References== Category:1992 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean male canoeists Category:Olympic canoeists of South Korea Category:Canoeists at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Canoeists at the 2014 Asian Games Category:Asian Games medalists in canoeing Category:Canoeists at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Medalists at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Asian Games silver medalists for South Korea
